1
00:00:00,317 --> 00:00:01,617
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,617 --> 00:00:03,017
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,468 --> 00:00:05,668
(Episode 45)

4
00:00:06,970 --> 00:00:08,637
I told you to get off
where you usually do.

5
00:00:08,637 --> 00:00:09,979
What if someone sees us?

6
00:00:10,081 --> 00:00:12,781
We got here 30 minutes early.
Who's going to see us?

7
00:00:14,673 --> 00:00:16,506
And I'm a patient, remember?

8
00:00:18,265 --> 00:00:20,265
You're not the only one with a cold.

9
00:00:20,913 --> 00:00:22,913
Can I ask you a favor? Today,

10
00:00:23,302 --> 00:00:25,744
could you please be careful
with the coughing?

11
00:00:25,744 --> 00:00:29,261
Like I can control when I cough.

12
00:00:29,372 --> 00:00:30,763
Go on before someone sees us.

13
00:00:38,922 --> 00:00:40,489
Team Manager Ko, Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

14
00:00:41,102 --> 00:00:42,312
Why are you two together?

15
00:00:43,445 --> 00:00:44,545
The thing is...

16
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:47,504
I happened to run into him
on the way here.

17
00:00:47,690 --> 00:00:49,090
I gave him a ride.

18
00:00:49,841 --> 00:00:52,041
We met right there in front of the office.

19
00:00:54,131 --> 00:00:55,131
Let's just go.

20
00:00:55,805 --> 00:00:57,005
Seriously.

21
00:01:04,203 --> 00:01:05,603
So you just ran into each other.

22
00:01:05,603 --> 00:01:08,103
I guess that's possible.

23
00:01:16,667 --> 00:01:18,167
Darn it.

24
00:01:22,463 --> 00:01:24,027
What do you want to talk about
this early in the morning?

25
00:01:24,852 --> 00:01:27,083
Don't tell me you're living
with Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

26
00:01:27,541 --> 00:01:29,899
- What?
- Just say yes or no.

27
00:01:30,452 --> 00:01:33,147
You're reading way too much
into us coming to work together once.

28
00:01:33,513 --> 00:01:34,513
Coming to work together once?

29
00:01:35,096 --> 00:01:37,296
Don't you think that one time was enough?

30
00:01:37,869 --> 00:01:38,869
What do you mean?

31
00:01:39,723 --> 00:01:42,423
I heard Ms. Cho's voice on the phone
when we talked over the weekend.

32
00:01:43,208 --> 00:01:44,819
It sounded like you two
were cleaning together.

33
00:01:45,873 --> 00:01:48,051
You eat together, catch colds together,

34
00:01:48,504 --> 00:01:49,709
and now you're coming to work together?

35
00:01:50,787 --> 00:01:52,299
Am I imagining things?

36
00:01:55,047 --> 00:01:57,805
You're right. I live with Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

37
00:01:58,868 --> 00:01:59,868
What?

38
00:02:00,065 --> 00:02:02,365
The place I moved into after moving out
turned out to be her house.

39
00:02:02,365 --> 00:02:04,976
And I had no idea it was her house
before I moved in.

40
00:02:05,184 --> 00:02:08,165
That's ridiculous.
How could you move in without knowing?

41
00:02:08,165 --> 00:02:10,112
If you don't want to believe it, don't.

42
00:02:10,244 --> 00:02:11,968
- Can I go now?
- Hold on.

43
00:02:13,597 --> 00:02:16,597
Keep the fact that you're living together
a secret at work.

44
00:02:17,111 --> 00:02:20,144
And if possible, find another place soon.

45
00:02:22,704 --> 00:02:24,224
Think about Seung Ri.

46
00:02:24,588 --> 00:02:26,672
I have no intention
of going around blabbing about it,

47
00:02:26,968 --> 00:02:28,544
so maybe you should watch yourself.

48
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:30,283
Grandma's sick.

49
00:02:31,796 --> 00:02:32,796
What?

50
00:02:32,796 --> 00:02:34,363
If you're worried, go see her.

51
00:02:35,544 --> 00:02:38,088
If you're not too busy dating, that is.

52
00:02:38,817 --> 00:02:39,884
All right. I'll stop by.

53
00:02:44,645 --> 00:02:45,885
Living with Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

54
00:02:47,792 --> 00:02:49,723
It's even more than I imagined.

55
00:02:58,993 --> 00:03:01,173
There's something I need to tell you,
Manager Seo.

56
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:03,419
If it's not work-related,
I'd rather not hear it.

57
00:03:03,608 --> 00:03:04,608
I'm busy.

58
00:03:04,812 --> 00:03:07,812
Sorry? Okay then.

59
00:03:17,225 --> 00:03:20,291
Ms. Cho, is the revised
Joy utilization plan finished?

60
00:03:20,577 --> 00:03:23,603
Sorry?
Yes, it'll be done in about an hour.

61
00:03:23,757 --> 00:03:26,357
Post it in the group chat when it's done,
and we'll meet after that.

62
00:03:27,023 --> 00:03:28,023
Yes, Team Manager.

63
00:03:34,492 --> 00:03:38,173
I didn't think
I needed to tell you how I feel.

64
00:03:39,059 --> 00:03:40,341
But I will.

65
00:03:41,630 --> 00:03:43,571
Yes.

66
00:03:45,032 --> 00:03:46,392
I like Team Manager Ko.

67
00:03:50,703 --> 00:03:51,703
Really?

68
00:03:52,732 --> 00:03:56,221
At first,
I didn't know what these feelings were,

69
00:03:57,163 --> 00:03:58,661
but now I'm sure.

70
00:03:59,812 --> 00:04:02,945
I like him.

71
00:04:05,409 --> 00:04:07,776
He'll be leaving in a few months.

72
00:04:08,830 --> 00:04:10,555
What are you going to do then?

73
00:04:11,588 --> 00:04:15,255
I'm trying not to think about things
that haven't happened yet.

74
00:04:16,475 --> 00:04:20,219
It's hard enough focusing
on how I feel right now.

75
00:04:21,972 --> 00:04:24,539
I'll be going now.

76
00:04:50,711 --> 00:04:53,056
Give me that. Your shoulders ache.

77
00:04:53,504 --> 00:04:55,589
What a thoughtful granddaughter.

78
00:04:55,589 --> 00:04:57,515
You never studied when you were told to.

79
00:04:57,718 --> 00:04:59,718
You know I was never good at studying.

80
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,660
And you're proud of that?

81
00:05:02,888 --> 00:05:04,221
Let's go.

82
00:05:04,701 --> 00:05:05,701
Hello.

83
00:05:05,701 --> 00:05:08,523
Hi. Taking Bit Na to kindergarten?

84
00:05:08,523 --> 00:05:11,667
Yes. Her mom's business trip
will last about a week.

85
00:05:11,943 --> 00:05:13,565
And Eun Hyeong's busy too.

86
00:05:14,276 --> 00:05:15,976
Bit Na, want me to take you today?

87
00:05:15,976 --> 00:05:16,976
Yes, Auntie.

88
00:05:17,463 --> 00:05:19,795
No way. You picked her up
and played with her yesterday.

89
00:05:19,795 --> 00:05:20,795
It's fine.

90
00:05:20,859 --> 00:05:23,165
I enjoy spending time with Bit Na.

91
00:05:23,165 --> 00:05:24,358
It's good exercise too.

92
00:05:24,358 --> 00:05:27,325
Right.
You're busy with the real estate office,

93
00:05:27,325 --> 00:05:29,309
housework, and studying.

94
00:05:29,937 --> 00:05:31,520
Bit Na, on the way,

95
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:33,053
want to play hopscotch there again?

96
00:05:33,284 --> 00:05:35,808
Yeah! I'll win today for sure.

97
00:05:36,011 --> 00:05:37,093
I'm going!

98
00:05:37,093 --> 00:05:40,269
All right, have fun.
I'll pick you up this afternoon.

99
00:05:40,416 --> 00:05:42,667
Okay. Bye-bye.

100
00:05:42,667 --> 00:05:44,091
See you later.

101
00:05:45,420 --> 00:05:49,917
Nothing's going on
with Eun Hyeong's family, right?

102
00:05:51,368 --> 00:05:52,741
No. Why would there be?

103
00:05:52,741 --> 00:05:56,075
Something just feels off.

104
00:05:57,423 --> 00:06:00,933
There's nothing going on
except that they have to move soon.

105
00:06:01,372 --> 00:06:04,739
Really? Guess I'm talking nonsense again.

106
00:06:05,252 --> 00:06:07,056
- Go on to work.
- Okay. You too.

107
00:06:07,056 --> 00:06:08,181
Yeah.

108
00:06:20,908 --> 00:06:22,075
(Eldest Son)

109
00:06:31,317 --> 00:06:33,955
Maybe they had an argument
about downsizing the house.

110
00:06:41,607 --> 00:06:45,328
Will you be able to catch those people?

111
00:06:45,852 --> 00:06:47,024
There's no way to know yet.

112
00:06:47,495 --> 00:06:49,795
For now,
they've been placed under a travel ban,

113
00:06:49,890 --> 00:06:51,208
and they're wanted, so please wait.

114
00:06:52,352 --> 00:06:54,416
Okay.

115
00:06:58,265 --> 00:06:59,395
The phone is turned off...

116
00:07:00,522 --> 00:07:02,677
Ji Seon, please answer.

117
00:07:06,496 --> 00:07:07,496
Honey!

118
00:07:08,641 --> 00:07:09,805
Are you okay?

119
00:07:10,665 --> 00:07:13,139
Where have you been?
Do you know how worried I was?

120
00:07:13,531 --> 00:07:14,531
Where's Bit Na?

121
00:07:15,641 --> 00:07:17,269
I asked Mother to watch her
for a few days.

122
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:19,883
No, forget that. Where have you been?

123
00:07:20,239 --> 00:07:22,221
You didn't answer your phone,
and you didn't go to your mother's.

124
00:07:22,849 --> 00:07:24,669
Where were you for two days?

125
00:07:26,876 --> 00:07:27,876
Cho Eun Hyeong,

126
00:07:29,995 --> 00:07:33,645
let's get a divorce.

127
00:07:35,165 --> 00:07:36,656
What is this all of a sudden?

128
00:07:37,173 --> 00:07:40,240
You're talking about divorce
over some scam?

129
00:07:40,668 --> 00:07:41,701
Some scam?

130
00:07:43,295 --> 00:07:45,267
That was our entire life savings.

131
00:07:47,388 --> 00:07:51,653
We have nowhere to go now.

132
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:54,888
I know, but divorce?

133
00:07:55,923 --> 00:07:58,229
If we have to leave this house right away,
we can stay in a tiny room,

134
00:07:58,546 --> 00:08:00,075
or with my parents for a while...

135
00:08:00,075 --> 00:08:03,613
Aren't you angry at me?

136
00:08:04,812 --> 00:08:08,504
Don't you hate me
for losing our entire deposit...

137
00:08:09,459 --> 00:08:11,576
because I got blinded by money?

138
00:08:12,657 --> 00:08:15,048
I do. I am angry.

139
00:08:16,006 --> 00:08:18,504
But it's not all your fault.

140
00:08:19,519 --> 00:08:22,861
It's also my fault
for always making you worry about money.

141
00:08:24,207 --> 00:08:27,739
Honey, so let's just
pull ourselves together and start over.

142
00:08:29,923 --> 00:08:33,256
How do we start over? How?

143
00:08:34,576 --> 00:08:38,720
How can we do that in this situation?

144
00:08:40,492 --> 00:08:42,845
Listen. Schopenhauer once said...

145
00:08:43,165 --> 00:08:44,899
that money is like seawater.

146
00:08:46,755 --> 00:08:49,043
The more you drink, the thirstier you get.

147
00:08:49,319 --> 00:08:51,893
That's what money is. So now we...

148
00:08:51,895 --> 00:08:54,659
Call it seawater or poison, whatever.

149
00:08:55,453 --> 00:08:57,432
We're just too different.

150
00:08:58,526 --> 00:09:00,848
If we keep living together,

151
00:09:01,365 --> 00:09:04,013
we'll only make each other more miserable.

152
00:09:04,013 --> 00:09:05,611
Everyone's different.

153
00:09:07,033 --> 00:09:10,333
But we're parents.
We have to think about Bit Na.

154
00:09:11,593 --> 00:09:14,589
I am. I'm doing this because of Bit Na.

155
00:09:14,719 --> 00:09:16,019
What are you talking about?

156
00:09:16,230 --> 00:09:18,897
We're completely bankrupt now.

157
00:09:20,096 --> 00:09:22,037
We have to move out of this house...

158
00:09:22,490 --> 00:09:25,787
and repay the loan we took out
for the deposit.

159
00:09:28,665 --> 00:09:32,555
I caused this, so I'll take responsibility
for all the debt.

160
00:09:33,344 --> 00:09:36,587
I won't let it affect you or Bit Na.

161
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:40,808
But I want you to raise her.

162
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:43,300
Honey, please!

163
00:09:43,300 --> 00:09:47,141
I'll pay child support as best as I can.

164
00:09:47,591 --> 00:09:48,832
And if you want,

165
00:09:49,270 --> 00:09:52,581
I'll give up custody. I'll give it all up.

166
00:09:54,199 --> 00:09:55,199
Cheon Ji Seon.

167
00:09:57,123 --> 00:10:00,323
How can you say that so easily?

168
00:10:01,922 --> 00:10:03,107
How can a mother...

169
00:10:04,215 --> 00:10:06,813
talk about giving up her child?

170
00:10:07,512 --> 00:10:09,779
This is my reality!

171
00:10:11,544 --> 00:10:13,305
To pay off all that debt,

172
00:10:13,305 --> 00:10:15,877
I'll have to take long-distance jobs
for years.

173
00:10:16,638 --> 00:10:18,605
If I'm away from home for days at a time,

174
00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:21,520
how am I supposed to raise Bit Na?

175
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,700
(Safe Password)

176
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:37,652
Then how many times...

177
00:10:42,072 --> 00:10:43,072
You called for me, sir?

178
00:10:44,052 --> 00:10:46,968
Mr. Cho,
there's something I'm curious about.

179
00:10:47,804 --> 00:10:51,004
A four-digit password...

180
00:10:51,688 --> 00:10:53,960
Is there any way to crack one?

181
00:10:54,523 --> 00:10:55,283
A password?

182
00:10:55,665 --> 00:10:58,592
It's nothing serious.

183
00:10:59,012 --> 00:11:01,712
I need to check something on an old phone,

184
00:11:02,259 --> 00:11:06,253
but I can't remember what password I set.

185
00:11:06,763 --> 00:11:10,211
So I just kept trying
random four-digit numbers,

186
00:11:10,957 --> 00:11:12,925
but nothing's working.

187
00:11:13,795 --> 00:11:16,309
Is there any way to figure it out?

188
00:11:18,528 --> 00:11:20,149
Theoretically, yes.

189
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:22,568
Really? How?

190
00:11:22,901 --> 00:11:25,083
You choose from the digits
zero through nine.

191
00:11:25,972 --> 00:11:27,363
For a four-digit code,

192
00:11:27,363 --> 00:11:29,757
the number of possibilities
is ten to the fourth power.

193
00:11:30,765 --> 00:11:31,883
A total of 10,000 combinations.

194
00:11:32,873 --> 00:11:34,392
What? 10,000...

195
00:11:34,957 --> 00:11:36,787
You're telling me to try 10,000 times?

196
00:11:36,787 --> 00:11:37,787
Are you messing with me?

197
00:11:38,117 --> 00:11:41,133
I don't want my fingers to fall off!

198
00:11:41,133 --> 00:11:44,269
To reduce the possibilities,
you can use permutations...

199
00:11:44,269 --> 00:11:47,421
Perm... What?

200
00:11:47,798 --> 00:11:48,931
Most people set passwords...

201
00:11:49,424 --> 00:11:52,229
using different digits.

202
00:11:52,229 --> 00:11:55,416
Assuming no digits repeat,

203
00:11:56,205 --> 00:11:57,403
ten factorial...

204
00:11:59,204 --> 00:12:00,204
Stop.

205
00:12:00,804 --> 00:12:03,671
You're making fun of me
because I failed math, aren't you?

206
00:12:04,365 --> 00:12:07,381
Because I slept through every math class
in high school?

207
00:12:07,381 --> 00:12:10,123
Forget factorials.
I need to open the safe...

208
00:12:10,373 --> 00:12:11,373
Darn it, the safe.

209
00:12:12,452 --> 00:12:16,368
Whatever it is, you should be able
to remember a password you set yourself.

210
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:19,227
Usually it's something
like a birthday or...

211
00:12:19,796 --> 00:12:23,459
That's exactly the problem.
I can't remember the birthday.

212
00:12:23,459 --> 00:12:26,136
That's why I'm so frustrated.

213
00:12:26,928 --> 00:12:27,928
Excuse me?

214
00:12:28,736 --> 00:12:30,213
Forget it.

215
00:12:31,481 --> 00:12:33,792
If you were trying
to raise my blood pressure, get out.

216
00:12:34,797 --> 00:12:36,675
I'd say mission accomplished.

217
00:12:37,655 --> 00:12:38,655
Then I'll be going.

218
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:41,160
Wait.

219
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:44,832
Your daughter and Team Manager Ko...

220
00:12:44,832 --> 00:12:47,085
seem to be dating these days.

221
00:12:48,539 --> 00:12:49,539
Sorry?

222
00:12:50,741 --> 00:12:52,024
So you didn't know.

223
00:12:52,386 --> 00:12:54,986
They're all lovey-dovey
from what I've seen.

224
00:12:55,542 --> 00:12:58,009
That can't be true.
There must be some misunderstanding.

225
00:12:59,060 --> 00:13:01,357
Misunderstanding? I may be bad at math,

226
00:13:01,857 --> 00:13:04,104
but when it comes to romance,
I'm an expert.

227
00:13:04,736 --> 00:13:05,736
The original master.

228
00:13:06,971 --> 00:13:09,355
But still, that kid...

229
00:13:09,355 --> 00:13:11,344
is leaving for the U.S. in a few months.

230
00:13:11,989 --> 00:13:13,752
I don't know what got into him.

231
00:13:15,621 --> 00:13:16,654
I'll take my leave.

232
00:13:18,241 --> 00:13:19,605
Go if you want.

233
00:13:20,039 --> 00:13:21,039
Fact...

234
00:13:21,778 --> 00:13:23,869
Factorial? What's a factorial?

235
00:13:24,511 --> 00:13:25,688
What is this?

236
00:13:27,932 --> 00:13:29,147
I have no idea what this means.

237
00:13:30,422 --> 00:13:33,256
So in the end,
Joy is a massive AI system...

238
00:13:33,256 --> 00:13:36,320
naturally integrated
throughout Our Happy Home?

239
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:39,973
Yes. And I'd like to expand Joy...

240
00:13:39,973 --> 00:13:41,112
into a companion AI for seniors.

241
00:13:41,632 --> 00:13:42,865
A companion AI?

242
00:13:43,219 --> 00:13:46,408
Yes. For example, if Joy says,
"Please feed me,"

243
00:13:46,408 --> 00:13:48,112
as a way of asking to be charged,

244
00:13:48,381 --> 00:13:51,120
the seniors won't see it
as just a function.

245
00:13:51,492 --> 00:13:54,547
They'll feel
like they're taking care of Joy.

246
00:13:54,816 --> 00:13:58,467
In short, I want them to feel rewarded
by caring for Joy.

247
00:13:59,014 --> 00:14:00,014
I love that idea.

248
00:14:00,014 --> 00:14:02,661
It's good to receive care,
but being able to care...

249
00:14:02,661 --> 00:14:04,872
for someone yourself
creates a sense of self-efficacy.

250
00:14:04,941 --> 00:14:06,261
Exactly. That's the point.

251
00:14:08,490 --> 00:14:10,941
It's late. Let's wrap up today's meeting.

252
00:14:11,497 --> 00:14:12,931
Thank you, everyone.

253
00:14:13,222 --> 00:14:14,222
Good work.

254
00:14:15,306 --> 00:14:16,325
Aren't you leaving, Ms. Cho?

255
00:14:16,706 --> 00:14:19,755
A little later.
I want to organize some ideas I just had.

256
00:14:20,270 --> 00:14:21,537
Then I'll get going.

257
00:14:22,096 --> 00:14:23,173
Okay. Good work.

258
00:14:29,544 --> 00:14:31,712
Don't go to the parking lot.

259
00:14:32,244 --> 00:14:34,344
Meet me where I dropped you off last time.
In 15 minutes.

260
00:14:35,181 --> 00:14:37,835
You go home alone today.
I need to visit my family.

261
00:14:38,665 --> 00:14:40,776
What? Did something happen?

262
00:14:41,985 --> 00:14:43,400
I heard my grandma isn't feeling well.

263
00:14:44,523 --> 00:14:46,832
How bad is it? Is she seriously ill?

264
00:14:47,298 --> 00:14:50,765
I'm not sure.
I'll go see her first and head home later.

265
00:14:51,807 --> 00:14:53,731
You should just stay there tonight
if you can.

266
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:55,797
You're really close to your grandmother.

267
00:14:56,752 --> 00:14:58,608
I'll see. Get home safe.

268
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:06,635
I hope it's nothing serious.

269
00:15:10,757 --> 00:15:12,709
How have you gotten so thin
in just a few days?

270
00:15:13,766 --> 00:15:14,933
Have you been to the hospital?

271
00:15:15,863 --> 00:15:17,533
There's no need.

272
00:15:18,008 --> 00:15:19,899
It's just a bit of fatigue.

273
00:15:21,053 --> 00:15:23,420
Is there something going on?

274
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:30,353
Grandma, is it that person
you mentioned before, the one you miss?

275
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:32,187
Are you looking for them?

276
00:15:33,893 --> 00:15:34,893
That's right.

277
00:15:36,140 --> 00:15:40,440
But so much time has passed
that it isn't easy.

278
00:15:41,817 --> 00:15:43,981
Can you tell me who it is?

279
00:15:44,332 --> 00:15:46,732
I'll do everything I can
to help find them.

280
00:15:47,241 --> 00:15:48,467
Don't worry about it.

281
00:15:49,416 --> 00:15:52,075
Your grandfather
is already doing a thorough search.

282
00:15:52,265 --> 00:15:56,152
So, did you and your grandma
have a nice long talk?

283
00:15:56,289 --> 00:15:59,059
Yes. Grandpa, how are you feeling?

284
00:15:59,692 --> 00:16:01,541
I've been so busy
taking care of your grandma...

285
00:16:02,012 --> 00:16:04,483
that I completely forgot
I was sick myself.

286
00:16:05,371 --> 00:16:08,604
Then I guess I'll have to stay sick.

287
00:16:08,604 --> 00:16:10,144
At least until you're fully recovered.

288
00:16:10,629 --> 00:16:12,853
What? No.

289
00:16:13,036 --> 00:16:15,503
I can handle being sick myself,
but not you being sick.

290
00:16:17,323 --> 00:16:20,853
You look happier than you did at home.
Are you really doing okay?

291
00:16:21,356 --> 00:16:22,523
Of course.

292
00:16:23,509 --> 00:16:27,509
Good. No matter where it is,
peace of mind is what matters most.

293
00:16:28,613 --> 00:16:31,691
So, is preparation
for the second round going well?

294
00:16:32,021 --> 00:16:33,621
Yes, I'm working hard on it.

295
00:16:34,433 --> 00:16:36,333
Good. I'm looking forward to it.

296
00:16:36,903 --> 00:16:37,903
Right.

297
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:41,656
This is a photo
from when you two went flower viewing.

298
00:16:41,828 --> 00:16:44,349
I've been busy,
so I only got it developed recently. Here.

299
00:16:45,945 --> 00:16:49,549
It turned out really well.

300
00:16:50,081 --> 00:16:53,120
I can't tell which one's the flower.

301
00:16:54,244 --> 00:16:55,851
Let me see too.

302
00:17:02,542 --> 00:17:04,661
Get well soon.

303
00:17:05,246 --> 00:17:07,446
Then we can go flower viewing again
together.

304
00:17:08,879 --> 00:17:10,412
I'm already all better.

305
00:17:10,801 --> 00:17:13,747
Let's go again tomorrow if you want.

306
00:17:15,338 --> 00:17:16,960
I'm going upstairs to gather some things.

307
00:17:17,125 --> 00:17:19,165
I left a lot behind
since I moved out in a hurry.

308
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:21,120
You're not staying the night?

309
00:17:22,134 --> 00:17:23,480
Maybe next time.

310
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:26,717
All right then.

311
00:17:27,245 --> 00:17:30,213
It's hard to focus when you're sleeping
in different places all the time.

312
00:17:30,849 --> 00:17:32,982
I'll get going then. Get some rest.

313
00:17:39,788 --> 00:17:40,955
You were right.

314
00:17:41,612 --> 00:17:45,779
He looks much more at ease
than he did at home.

315
00:17:49,645 --> 00:17:51,979
His grandmother must be pretty sick...

316
00:17:52,511 --> 00:17:54,480
if your Team Manager
just headed home like that.

317
00:17:54,616 --> 00:17:58,383
Yeah, I think so.
He looked really worried.

318
00:18:02,325 --> 00:18:03,958
Dad, why do you keep staring at her?

319
00:18:04,736 --> 00:18:06,752
You've been doing it all through dinner.

320
00:18:10,287 --> 00:18:12,187
Me? No, I haven't.

321
00:18:14,504 --> 00:18:17,565
Should I make something
and send it through you tomorrow?

322
00:18:17,922 --> 00:18:18,922
Food?

323
00:18:19,292 --> 00:18:22,251
She's elderly. I was worried
she might've overexerted herself...

324
00:18:22,673 --> 00:18:24,179
making all that food that day.

325
00:18:24,931 --> 00:18:26,691
I was thinking of making some porridge.

326
00:18:27,579 --> 00:18:28,725
That's overdoing it, Mom.

327
00:18:29,145 --> 00:18:31,949
A family like theirs
probably has a housekeeper...

328
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:33,160
and a daughter-in-law too.

329
00:18:34,112 --> 00:18:35,112
You think so?

330
00:18:35,599 --> 00:18:38,800
Still, that daughter-in-law
doesn't seem very attentive.

331
00:18:39,317 --> 00:18:41,688
You mean the Team Manager's mother?

332
00:18:41,979 --> 00:18:43,679
What's wrong with her?

333
00:18:44,196 --> 00:18:46,776
Don't even get me started. She's so...

334
00:18:47,236 --> 00:18:48,236
Stop.

335
00:18:49,081 --> 00:18:51,781
Honestly, not in front of the kids.

336
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:56,325
Sorry. I shouldn't have said that.

337
00:18:58,031 --> 00:19:01,309
Bit Na, how many more nights
until your mom comes back?

338
00:19:02,547 --> 00:19:04,013
I don't know.

339
00:19:07,212 --> 00:19:10,016
Looks like Bit Na's sleepy.
Let's go sleep with Grandma.

340
00:19:10,813 --> 00:19:12,346
- My little princess.
- You two should head upstairs too.

341
00:19:12,346 --> 00:19:14,046
- Come on, Bit Na.
- Okay. Good night.

342
00:19:14,046 --> 00:19:15,432
- Sleep well.
- All right.

343
00:19:15,432 --> 00:19:16,632
- Good night.
- Let's go.

344
00:19:17,771 --> 00:19:18,944
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

345
00:19:18,944 --> 00:19:19,821
- Rock, paper.
- Rock, paper.

346
00:19:19,821 --> 00:19:21,531
One more time. Rock, paper, scissors.

347
00:19:21,531 --> 00:19:23,811
Why are you playing rock-paper-scissors
every night?

348
00:19:23,811 --> 00:19:26,347
Bit Na,
I think your aunts are aging backwards.

349
00:19:26,347 --> 00:19:29,214
- Come on, let's go.
- Let's go, princess.

350
00:19:33,934 --> 00:19:36,733
So we have to enter numbers 10,000 times?

351
00:19:38,017 --> 00:19:40,949
What if Father passes away
before we even see the will...

352
00:19:41,581 --> 00:19:44,325
Hey, watch your mouth.

353
00:19:47,896 --> 00:19:50,381
- Gyeol, are you leaving already?
- Yes.

354
00:19:50,381 --> 00:19:52,669
You rarely come by.
Why not stay the night?

355
00:19:53,124 --> 00:19:54,427
What are you talking about?

356
00:19:54,428 --> 00:19:57,595
Whether you're a man or a woman,
you shouldn't keep changing beds.

357
00:19:58,081 --> 00:20:00,613
But why is that all you're taking?

358
00:20:00,950 --> 00:20:03,563
Why not move everything at once?

359
00:20:04,031 --> 00:20:05,603
I'm only staying there for a few months.

360
00:20:05,878 --> 00:20:07,445
I'll just bring things as I need them.

361
00:20:08,028 --> 00:20:10,915
By the way, Gyeol,
it seems like you're dating these days.

362
00:20:11,202 --> 00:20:12,733
- Excuse me?
- Mr. Cho's daughter.

363
00:20:12,733 --> 00:20:15,797
I saw you two having a lunch date.

364
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:20,296
That's right.
I also snuck onto your laptop and saw...

365
00:20:24,368 --> 00:20:28,139
Well,
why did you make your password so simple?

366
00:20:28,694 --> 00:20:31,624
Seriously. Apologize.
Why were you snooping through his laptop?

367
00:20:32,891 --> 00:20:34,368
You wanted to see it too...

368
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:37,563
I'll be going now. Good night.

369
00:20:37,973 --> 00:20:41,304
Right. Get there safe.

370
00:20:43,353 --> 00:20:44,353
What?

371
00:20:45,196 --> 00:20:48,480
Come on, who uses 0000 as a password?

372
00:20:51,428 --> 00:20:54,411
Could Father's safe password be 0000 too?

373
00:20:55,349 --> 00:20:57,704
Then was that kid
born on month zero, day zero?

374
00:20:59,824 --> 00:21:00,824
Really?

375
00:21:01,182 --> 00:21:03,339
Starting tomorrow,
you're only going to the studio at night?

376
00:21:03,563 --> 00:21:06,808
Yeah. That writer says
she can't work if someone's there.

377
00:21:07,447 --> 00:21:10,584
So we're doing
nights for you, days for you.

378
00:21:10,868 --> 00:21:12,320
No, days for you, nights for me.

379
00:21:12,623 --> 00:21:14,216
What does that even mean?

380
00:21:14,341 --> 00:21:16,024
Days, you. Nights, me.

381
00:21:16,460 --> 00:21:18,952
Hey, watch it. Calling your mom "you?"

382
00:21:19,129 --> 00:21:21,744
Still, don't ruin your health
pulling all-nighters.

383
00:21:22,235 --> 00:21:24,176
You need to divide your time more evenly.

384
00:21:24,176 --> 00:21:25,176
Evenly?

385
00:21:26,257 --> 00:21:29,973
Honestly,
that writer and I are like oil and water.

386
00:21:31,317 --> 00:21:32,989
One of these days,
I'm really going to get back at her.

387
00:21:33,212 --> 00:21:35,765
Hey, you shouldn't say that.
If you're working together,

388
00:21:36,236 --> 00:21:39,707
you need to get along. Right, honey?

389
00:21:39,807 --> 00:21:42,656
I thought you said she respected you.
Was that all a lie?

390
00:21:42,656 --> 00:21:44,623
Not entirely.

391
00:21:44,623 --> 00:21:47,123
She did accept me as a co-creator.

392
00:21:48,125 --> 00:21:51,272
Why don't you bring something tasty
to the studio sometime?

393
00:21:51,853 --> 00:21:54,531
Maybe she and Seung Wu can become friends.

394
00:21:54,617 --> 00:21:57,605
Seo Seung Wu, you're an artist
with a contract, just like her.

395
00:21:57,976 --> 00:21:59,609
Don't let yourself feel small, okay?

396
00:22:09,628 --> 00:22:11,883
When I think about it,
you're really good...

397
00:22:12,039 --> 00:22:14,288
at understanding your children.

398
00:22:15,076 --> 00:22:17,397
But when it comes to Mom,
you're a total failure.

399
00:22:17,757 --> 00:22:19,211
You think I'm a failure too?

400
00:22:19,354 --> 00:22:22,854
Mom gets all frustrated inside, right?

401
00:22:23,211 --> 00:22:26,027
And all you have to do
is help her work through it.

402
00:22:26,530 --> 00:22:29,197
But every time,
you just escape to your study.

403
00:22:29,785 --> 00:22:31,352
How is she supposed to feel better?

404
00:22:32,408 --> 00:22:36,808
What can I do to cheer Mom up?

405
00:22:37,420 --> 00:22:38,420
That's easy.

406
00:22:39,311 --> 00:22:42,339
A gift. Something that would move her.

407
00:22:43,049 --> 00:22:46,197
And what would that be?

408
00:22:49,072 --> 00:22:52,547
I hear women like small, shiny things.

409
00:22:52,796 --> 00:22:54,063
Small, shiny things?

410
00:22:55,301 --> 00:22:56,432
Like what?

411
00:22:57,871 --> 00:22:58,931
I don't know.

412
00:22:59,441 --> 00:23:01,641
If Seo Seung Ri were here,
she'd figure it out right away.

413
00:23:03,252 --> 00:23:04,400
Why isn't she here, anyway?

414
00:23:11,901 --> 00:23:13,834
You really didn't have to take me home.

415
00:23:14,300 --> 00:23:15,600
How could I not?

416
00:23:16,040 --> 00:23:18,621
Our team's ace willingly worked late
to prepare for the competition.

417
00:23:18,976 --> 00:23:20,712
The least I can do
is make sure she gets home safely.

418
00:23:21,868 --> 00:23:23,613
You should go. See you tomorrow.

419
00:23:24,672 --> 00:23:25,808
Manager Seo.

420
00:23:28,577 --> 00:23:29,869
This weekend, maybe...

421
00:23:30,614 --> 00:23:32,514
Okay. I'll come in to work.

422
00:23:32,514 --> 00:23:34,081
No, not work.

423
00:23:34,501 --> 00:23:35,901
Let's go on a date.

424
00:23:37,397 --> 00:23:39,739
Forget it. That slipped out.

425
00:23:40,714 --> 00:23:42,227
Let's do some fieldwork.

426
00:23:43,790 --> 00:23:46,037
Can I pick the location?

427
00:23:48,039 --> 00:23:49,464
Of course.

428
00:23:50,465 --> 00:23:51,465
Where should we go?

429
00:23:51,846 --> 00:23:54,213
Let me think about it.

430
00:23:55,052 --> 00:23:56,552
- Then...
- Okay.

431
00:24:01,501 --> 00:24:04,488
Did she just accept my date invitation?

432
00:24:10,506 --> 00:24:12,539
No way.

433
00:24:13,133 --> 00:24:14,213
Yes!

434
00:24:25,843 --> 00:24:28,835
Are you still upset because I kept quiet
about the Chairman's family?

435
00:24:30,904 --> 00:24:34,307
It wasn't something
I could just tell anyone.

436
00:24:34,585 --> 00:24:36,408
I wish you'd try to understand that.

437
00:24:39,593 --> 00:24:40,660
Honey.

438
00:24:42,752 --> 00:24:44,331
Are you not even going to talk
to me anymore?

439
00:24:45,969 --> 00:24:48,989
You keep your mouth shut all day.
You think I can't do the same?

440
00:24:49,580 --> 00:24:51,893
From now on,

441
00:24:51,893 --> 00:24:53,925
I'll keep my mouth shut too,
so don't talk to me.

442
00:25:01,855 --> 00:25:03,413
Do we have a visitor?

443
00:25:04,836 --> 00:25:06,227
Hello, Chairman.

444
00:25:06,551 --> 00:25:08,757
Welcome.

445
00:25:09,052 --> 00:25:11,533
Ms. Kang Yeon Ja, what brings you here?

446
00:25:11,853 --> 00:25:13,912
I heard Madam wasn't feeling well,

447
00:25:14,557 --> 00:25:16,872
so I brought some oxtail soup.

448
00:25:17,993 --> 00:25:19,083
Oxtail soup?

449
00:25:19,747 --> 00:25:21,968
We happened to share a meal...

450
00:25:22,389 --> 00:25:24,101
outside the hospital the other day,

451
00:25:24,323 --> 00:25:27,245
and I remembered
how much she enjoyed the soup then.

452
00:25:28,431 --> 00:25:30,003
How thoughtful of you.

453
00:25:30,379 --> 00:25:31,445
Not at all.

454
00:25:32,487 --> 00:25:34,253
And I have something to return as well.

455
00:25:34,473 --> 00:25:37,221
Would it be all right
if I saw Madam for a moment?

456
00:25:37,694 --> 00:25:40,771
Of course. She's awake right now.
Go on in.

457
00:25:40,949 --> 00:25:42,469
Thank you.

458
00:25:46,907 --> 00:25:47,907
Something to return?

459
00:25:49,449 --> 00:25:51,249
What's this, another Yu Jeong Ran?

460
00:25:51,664 --> 00:25:53,231
What are you hoping to get out of this?

461
00:26:11,247 --> 00:26:12,920
Ma'am, I'm here.

462
00:26:14,921 --> 00:26:17,254
Well, look who it is. Come in.

463
00:26:17,952 --> 00:26:19,152
Please stay seated.

464
00:26:20,166 --> 00:26:23,336
I heard you've been quite ill.
How are you feeling?

465
00:26:23,595 --> 00:26:27,120
I'm all better now. Here, have a seat.

466
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:59,320
(Our Happy Days)

467
00:26:59,657 --> 00:27:01,760
Gyeol has recently fallen for someone.

468
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:03,379
Seung Ri knows about it too.

469
00:27:03,379 --> 00:27:06,379
I don't intend to keep watching her suffer
because of him.

470
00:27:06,595 --> 00:27:08,571
I'm going to make Seung Ri happy,
no matter what.

471
00:27:08,571 --> 00:27:10,871
I've gotten so used to commuting
by scooter...

472
00:27:10,871 --> 00:27:12,204
that I have no desire
to take the bus anymore.

473
00:27:15,133 --> 00:27:17,033
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
